To set up the Spam Classifier Web App on your local machine, please follow these steps:

Step 1: Clone the Repository
Clone the repository to your local machine using the following command:
git clone https://github.com/your-username/spam-classifier-web-app.git

Step 2: Update File Paths
Before running the application, update the file paths in the app.py file to match the directory structure on your machine.
Update the paths for spam_classifier_model.h5 and tokenizer.pickle files in the app.py file to reflect their locations on your machine.

Step 3: Create Templates Directory
Create a templates directory in the project root directory if it doesn't already exist. Place the index.html file inside this directory.

Step 4: Install Dependencies
Install the required dependencies listed in the requirements.txt file using pip:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Step 5: Run the Application
Run the Flask application by executing the app.py file:
python app.py

Step 6: Access the Web App
Access the web app by navigating to http://localhost:8080 in your web browser.
